<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Morphological description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Frustule low-cylindrical, valve diameter is 3.2-3.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, a clear boundary between edge and central zone is absent, striae wedge-shaped, 18-20 in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, central process is absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. SEM (A-E, G, H) and LM images (F) of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city, valve views: A Cyclotella cryptica B Cyclotella marina C, D Cyclotella meduanae E, F Cyclotella meneghiniana G Cyclostephanos dubius H Cyclostephanos invisitatus, with arrows shown on A, D, H marginal and central fultoportulae, B marginal fultoportulae, F central fultoportulae. Scale bars: 2 μm (B, D); 4 μm (A); 5 μm (C, E); 10 μm (F-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545739" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">7B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
According to literature data, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="C. marina" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="marina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">C. marina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a high ecological relevance, with a preference in brackish waters, also inhabiting marine environments even with salinity ranges around 30‰; smaller numbers were recorded for freshwaters under 10‰ (
<bibRefCitation author="Tanimura, Y" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the National Science Museum Series C" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="5 - 11" refId="B122" refString="Tanimura, Y, Naqumo, T, Kato, M, 2004. A new variety of Cyclotella atomus from Tokyo Bay, Japan: C. atomus var. marina var. nov. Bulletin of the National Science Museum Series C 30: 5 - 11" title="A new variety of Cyclotella atomus from Tokyo Bay, Japan: C. atomus var. marina var. nov." volume="30" year="2004">Tanimura et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4490/algae.2010.25.2.057" author="Chung, MH" journalOrPublisher="Algae - Korean Phycological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="57 - 64" refId="B23" refString="Chung, MH, Yoon, WD, Lee, J-B, 2010. Morphological description of Cyclotella atomus var. marina (Bacillariophyceae): Newly reported in Korean waters. Algae - Korean Phycological Society 25 (2): 57 - 64, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4490/algae.2010.25.2.057" title="Morphological description of Cyclotella atomus var. marina (Bacillariophyceae): Newly reported in Korean waters." url="https://doi.org/10.4490/algae.2010.25.2.057" volume="25" year="2010">Chung et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ake-Castillo, JA" journalOrPublisher="Nova Hedwigia" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="263 - 274" refId="B1" refString="Ake-Castillo, JA, Okolodkov, YB, Espinosa-Matias, S, Merino-Virgilio, FC, Herrera-Silveira, JA, Ector, L, 2012. Cyclotella marina (Tanimura, Nagumo et Kato) Ake-Castillo, Okolodkov et Ector comb. et stat. nov. (Thalassiosiraceae): A bloom-forming diatom in the southeastern Gulf of Mexico. Nova Hedwigia 141: 263 - 274" title="Cyclotella marina (Tanimura, Nagumo et Kato) Ake-Castillo, Okolodkov et Ector comb. et stat. nov. (Thalassiosiraceae): A bloom-forming diatom in the southeastern Gulf of Mexico." volume="141" year="2012">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Aké-Castillo">Ake-Castillo</normalizedToken>
et al. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
). There are known cases where 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="C. marina" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="marina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">C. marina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exists in shallow waters with freshwater discharges. At the same time, the appearance of this taxon is connected to high nutrient concentrations. In addition, cases of blooming of this species are known in the south-eastern Gulf of Mexico (
<bibRefCitation author="Ake-Castillo, JA" journalOrPublisher="Nova Hedwigia" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="263 - 274" refId="B1" refString="Ake-Castillo, JA, Okolodkov, YB, Espinosa-Matias, S, Merino-Virgilio, FC, Herrera-Silveira, JA, Ector, L, 2012. Cyclotella marina (Tanimura, Nagumo et Kato) Ake-Castillo, Okolodkov et Ector comb. et stat. nov. (Thalassiosiraceae): A bloom-forming diatom in the southeastern Gulf of Mexico. Nova Hedwigia 141: 263 - 274" title="Cyclotella marina (Tanimura, Nagumo et Kato) Ake-Castillo, Okolodkov et Ector comb. et stat. nov. (Thalassiosiraceae): A bloom-forming diatom in the southeastern Gulf of Mexico." volume="141" year="2012">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Aké-Castillo">Ake-Castillo</normalizedToken>
et al. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="C. marina" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="marina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">C. marina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in epilithic benthic samples at all investigated sites during this research for the Southern Bug River (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Species composition of centric diatoms at the investigated sites near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in the year 2017 (2013 added for station 2)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" tableUuid="DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677">1</tableCitation>
). For Ukrainian territory it is also reported from Khmelnytskyy NPS, (
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Algologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="431 - 440" refId="B44" refString="Genkal, SI, Yarmoshenko, LP, Okhapkin, AG, 2012. First records on marine species Cyclotella marina (Bacillariophyta) in freshwaters of Europe. Algologia 22 (4): 431 - 440" title="First records on marine species Cyclotella marina (Bacillariophyta) in freshwaters of Europe." volume="22" year="2012">Genkal et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
) and in phytoplankton in Odessa Bay of the Black Sea (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v50.i4.40" author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Hydrobiological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="38 - 49" refId="B42" refString="Genkal, SI, Terenko, LM, 2014. New data on flora of centric diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Black Sea. Hydrobiological Journal 50 (2): 38 - 49, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v50.i4.40" title="New data on flora of centric diatoms (Centrophyceae) of the Black Sea." url="https://doi.org/10.1615/HydrobJ.v50.i4.40" volume="50" year="2014">Genkal and Terenko 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
It is also a common species for Europe, North America, and Asia (
<bibRefCitation author="Ake-Castillo, JA" journalOrPublisher="Nova Hedwigia" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="263 - 274" refId="B1" refString="Ake-Castillo, JA, Okolodkov, YB, Espinosa-Matias, S, Merino-Virgilio, FC, Herrera-Silveira, JA, Ector, L, 2012. Cyclotella marina (Tanimura, Nagumo et Kato) Ake-Castillo, Okolodkov et Ector comb. et stat. nov. (Thalassiosiraceae): A bloom-forming diatom in the southeastern Gulf of Mexico. Nova Hedwigia 141: 263 - 274" title="Cyclotella marina (Tanimura, Nagumo et Kato) Ake-Castillo, Okolodkov et Ector comb. et stat. nov. (Thalassiosiraceae): A bloom-forming diatom in the southeastern Gulf of Mexico." volume="141" year="2012">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Aké-Castillo">Ake-Castillo</normalizedToken>
et al. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Algologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="431 - 440" refId="B44" refString="Genkal, SI, Yarmoshenko, LP, Okhapkin, AG, 2012. First records on marine species Cyclotella marina (Bacillariophyta) in freshwaters of Europe. Algologia 22 (4): 431 - 440" title="First records on marine species Cyclotella marina (Bacillariophyta) in freshwaters of Europe." volume="22" year="2012">Genkal et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Guiry, MD" journalOrPublisher="Diatom Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" publicationUrl="https://www.algaebase.org" refId="B48" refString="Guiry, MD, Guiry, GM, 2021. AlgaeBase. World-wide electronic publication, National University of Ireland, Galway. https://www.algaebase.org" title="AlgaeBase. World-wide electronic publication, National University of Ireland, Galway." url="https://www.algaebase.org" year="2021">Guiry and Guiry 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
